  "description": "Annual warm-season fruiting crop (Solanum lycopersicum, 60–90 days to first fruit). Indeterminate varieties produce continuously; determinate varieties produce in concentrated burst. Requires staking (indeterminate) or support. Deep transplant burial for adventitious root development. Buzz-pollinated by bumblebees (greenhouse production needs mechanical vibration). Wide cultivar diversity including cherry, paste, beefsteak, and heirloom types.",
